sentences: Madeleine Isaksson (born 1956) is a Swedish/French composer.
Madeleine Isaksson studied at the Royal Academy of Music in Stockholm from 1979 to 1987.
In 1987 she lived in Amsterdam for a year of studies with the composer Louis Andriessen.
In 1987 she lived in Amsterdam for a year of studies with the composer Louis Andriessen.
In the early 1990s, she moved to France, where she lives and works near Paris.
